snippet.textDisplay: <3

Seeing murdoc being left out here and going back to humility, it makes me have a new interpretation of the song, what if 2d was singing about how he thought he needed Murdock and ponders if bringing him back to the band, to their "friendship" would work out. There are some verses that points to that

"I'm the lonely twin, the left hand
Reset myself and get back on track
I don't want this isolation
See the state I'm in now?

Callin' the hunter with a rifle"

Here he's taking about how he thinks his success and wellbeing are due to Murdock leadership, but at the end, he knows that Murdock is a bad mate to have around.

"If I pick it up when I know that it's broken
Do I put it back?"

This is him pondering if he should give a chance to Murdock after all his bullshit, even though he knows Murdock is a dick by nature.

After all that we see Murdock here, all by himself, 2-d made a choice, he will be the leader of his own life, he will not follow Murdock anymore.

Oh, and did you notice that his eyes are white just like when he was happy and confident in humility? Good for him.
